                  <div class="bt_bb_wrapper">
                  <div class="bodytext contentText"> <p>Your air ducts are an important part of your home's heating and cooling. <br><br>When well maintained, your ducts allow your HVAC system to do its job, keeping you comfortable in your home, keeping pollutants out, and keeping your house dust-free. If your ducts are dirty or clogged, numerous problems could potentially arise, including higher energy bills and health problems for you and your family.<br><br></p> </div>
                  <div class="bodytext contentText"> <p>Today, we're going to discuss a few of the biggest benefits of regular duct cleaning and how learning how to clean your ducts can prevent big issues down the road. Your air ducts are like your home's lungs; treat them right and you won't have to worry.<br><br></p><h2 class="subtitle">Clean Ducts Prevent Health Issues<br><br></h2><p>One of the biggest problems, when you leave your ducts to collect dirt and debris, is <a href="/blogs/dirty-air-ducts-can-affect-your-health" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="link_clicked">the health problems</a> that it might cause those in your home. In the worst cases, you may have mould growing in there, which can be extremely harmful and potentially deadly. But, even in milder cases, having too much dust in the home can cause issues.<br><br>If anyone in the house has allergies, an influx of dust being blown out of your air ducts will make their lives miserable. Allergies can come in many forms, including skin irritation and respiratory problems, but these conditions can worsen over time and become more threatening. In younger children, this can develop into asthma, which can last a lifetime.</p><h2 class="subtitle"><br>Get Rid of Mould<br><br></h2><p>Unclean ductwork can be a hotbed for moisture, which can quickly lead to <a href="https://www.gov.mb.ca/health/publichealth/environmentalhealth/indoor.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="link_clicked">mould growth</a>. The biggest problem with mould is that it's incredibly hard to detect but it spreads quickly and poses a lot of health risks. When it gets out of hand, mould can spread into your walls and floors, costing you thousands in treatment.<br><br>If left untreated, as we've discussed, mould exposure can cause serious respiratory issues, and even lead to mental health problems and cancer in the worst scenarios.<br><br></p><h2 class="subtitle">Improve Your Indoor Air Quality<br><br></h2><p>When your ducts are bombarded with dust, allergens, pet dander, and other debris, your HVAC system is going to suffer. Proper maintenance of your ducts will improve your system's performance and help provide you with clean and well-distributed air in your home.<br><br>It'll also keep your HVAC system going. If you're cleaning regularly, you'll reduce the amount of money you'll have to spend on heating and cooling maintenance and add years on to your system's lifespan.</p><h2 class="subtitle"><br>Boost Your Home's Energy Efficiency<br><br></h2><p>Clogged up ducts make your HVAC system work harder, which makes your <a href="https://efficiencymb.ca/#:~:text=Energy%20efficiency%20has%20made%20huge%20strides%20over%20the%20past%20several%20decades.&amp;text=Efficiency%20Manitoba%20is%20Manitoba's%20newest,easy%2C%20affordable%2C%20and%20satisfying." target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="link_clicked">monthly energy bills</a> skyrocket. Regular cleanings may seem like more work and maybe more money at the time, but it's going to be worth it when you see your lower energy bill every month. <br><br></p><h2 class="subtitle">Get Your Duct Cleaning Done Properly</h2><p><br>Now that you know how important regular duct cleaning is for your health, comfort, and finances, it's time to take action. You can try to perform duct maintenance on your own, but if you want it done the right way, <a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/winnipeg-hvac-company-contact" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">contact us</a> at East Side Ventilation. We're Winnipeg's #1 choice for residential HVAC installation, repair, and <a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/residential-duct-cleaning-winnipeg" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">duct cleaning</a>. No matter what state your ducts are in, we'll be able to help you clean them, so you can enjoy clean, safe air in your home.</p><p>&nbsp;</p> </div>
